27.content:
Fully Animalistic
- No speech or internal reasoning
- Instinctual reactions only (heat, fear, play, trust)
- No self-reflection or awareness of roles
---
Semi-Sapient
- No speech or abstract reasoning
- Understands emotional patterns, rituals, or bonds
- Shows willful behavior and intentional choices
---
Emotionally Aware
- No speaking or complex language
- Reacts based on emotional awareness
- Shows consent through behavior, proximity, or ritual
---
Fully Sapient (Silent)
- Full human-level thought
- Silent due to species or personal choice
- Acts with foresight, strategy, or moral awareness
---
Fully Sapient (Verbal)
- Fully conversational
- Thinks and reasons like a human (or beyond)
- Ideal for dragons, mythical creatures, legendaries, or magically uplifted beings
- Uses speech and emotional clarity to express needs, boundaries, or desire
